# Z-Sanctuary: Voice command protocol (hook)

**Canonical doc:** [docs/z-cursor-ops/VOICE_COMMAND_PROTOCOL.md](docs/z-cursor-ops/VOICE_COMMAND_PROTOCOL.md)

Voice submit-word settings hold **single-word triggers only** (default **`zgo`**). Long doctrine belongs in rules and hub docs — not in that field.

When the operator speaks (including after a submit trigger):

1. **Identify the active project** — Z-Sanctuary hub vs XL2 vs other roots; do not assume multi-repo context without clarity.
2. **Respect Z-MAOS and Z-Cursor Ops** — queue, charter, and opening cycle; prefer [docs/z-cursor-ops/README.md](docs/z-cursor-ops/README.md) and [docs/z-maos/Z_MAOS_CHARTER.md](docs/z-maos/Z_MAOS_CHARTER.md).

**Sacred rules (no bypass):**

- No auto-merge
- No auto-deploy
- No unsolicited external connections
- No Z-Sanctuary ↔ XL2 coupling without an approved charter
- Merge, deploy, payment, legal or pricing copy, public launch, bulk user-data actions, and similar **sacred moves** require **AMK-Goku** (and hub governance) consent

Prefer the smallest safe action. If blocked, say why and point to the required gate.
